":"Gowran, Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Irland","County Kilkenny, Ireland":"County Kilkenny, Irland"},"nl":{"1396–21 April 1476":"1396–21 april 1476","1396–1476":"1396–1476","1410–1506":"1410–1506","1425–1465":"1425–1465","1440–1508":"1440–1508","1370–1431":"1370–1431","1380–Female":"1380–Overleden","21 April 1476":"21 april 1476","1396":"1396","1440":"1440","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","1425":"1425","1465":"1465","1410":"1410","1476":"1476","1431":"1431","about 1425":"circa 1425","1508":"1508","1506":"1506","Hillsborough Castle, County Down, Ireland":"Hillsborough Castle, County Down, Ierland","Leinster, Kildare, Ireland":"Leinster, Ierland","Ulster, Ireland":"Ulster, Ierland","Ferns, County Wexford, Ireland":"Ferns, County Wexford, Ierland","Gowran, Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Ireland":"Gowran, Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Ierland","County Kilkenny, Ireland":"County Kilkenny, Ierland"},"en":{"1396–21 April 1476":"1396–21 April 1476","1396–1476":"1396–1476","1410–1506":"1410–1506","1425–1465":"1425–1465","1440–1508":"1440–1508","1370–1431":"1370–1431","1380–Female":"1380–Deceased","21 April 1476":"21 April 1476","1396":"1396","1440":"1440","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","1425":"1425","1465":"1465","1410":"1410","1476":"1476","1431":"1431","about 1425":"about 1425","1508":"1508","1506":"1506","Hillsborough Castle, County Down, Ireland":"Hillsborough Castle, County Down, Ireland","Leinster, Kildare, Ireland":"Leinster, Ireland","Ulster, Ireland":"Ulster, Ireland","Ferns, County Wexford, Ireland":"Ferns, County Wexford, Ireland","Gowran, Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Ireland":"Gowran, Kilkenny, County Kilkenny, Ireland","County Kilkenny, Ireland":"County Kilkenny, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Kavanaugh","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Oonagh.","Irish: variant of   Kavanagh  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Kavanagh","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Aidan, Aileen, Brendan, Cathal, Conor, Eamon, Keelin, Liam, Michael Sean, Niall, Ronan, Sean Patrick.","Irish: from <b>Caomhánach</b>, an adjectival epithet meaning ‘belonging to (Saint) <i>Caomhán</i>’, whose personal name means ‘little beautiful one’. Etymologically, the first part of the name is the same as that in   Kevin  .","History: The first known bearer of the epithet was Domhnall Caomhánach (Donal Kavanagh, died in 1175), the son of Diarmait Mac Murchadha (Dermot McMurrough), king of Leinster in the 12th century. Despite being killed at an early age, Domhnall Caomhánach gave his name to a large and important family in Irish history."]}]},{"name":"Donald","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of Gaelic Domhnall . The final <i>-d</i> of the Anglicized form derives partly from misinterpretation by English speakers of the Gaelic pronunciation, and partly from association with Germanic-origin names such as   Ronald .  This name is strongly associated with clan Macdonald, the clan of the medieval Lords of the Isles, but is now also widely used by families with no Scottish connections."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Reagh","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Ute.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Riabhach</b>, which MacLysaght describes as an adjectival surname (meaning ‘gray’ or ‘brindled’) that ‘took the place of an hereditary one’.","Possibly an altered form of German   Rech  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Rech","meanings":["From Italian <b>Rocco</b>; ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Donald Reagh Kavanaugh was born in 1396, in Ferns, County Wexford, Ireland, his father, Lord Gerald Kavanagh of Fern, was 26 and his mother, Mrs. Gerald Kavanagh, was 17. He had at least 2 daughters with Catherine O'Nolan. He died on 21 April 1476, in County Kilkenny, Ireland,